I find it hard to memorize words that come and go on the screen. It is challenging for me.
MR CLARK GREW UP IN A LIBRARY.
WHEN HE WAS YOUNG HIS FAMILY LIVED IN A SMALL APARTMENT.
HE THOUGHT THAT THEY WERE RICH AND WELL OFF, BUT THEY WERE ACTUALLY VERY POOR.
HIS FATHER WAS HIRED AS A CUSTODIAN FOR THE LOCAL LIBRARY AND HIS FAMILY GOT TO MOVE IN THERE.
HIS FATHER KEPT THE LIBRARY EXTREMELY CLEAN AND NEAT.
HE EVEN WAXED THE TOP OF THE BOOK SHELVES.
MR CLARK DIDN'T WANT TO BRING FRIENDS TO HIS HOUSE BECAUSE IT WAS SO DIFFERENT THAN ANYONE ELSE'S HOME.
HE HAD TO BE VERY QUIET DURING THE OPEN HOURS, BUT ONCE THE LIBRARY CLOSED HE COULD BE AS LOUD AND ENERGETIC AS HE WANTED.
AT NIGHT HE WOULD WAKE UP WITH A QUESTION AND GO FIND THE BOOK THAT HAD THE ANSWER TO HIS QUESTION, OFTEN STAYING AWAKE UNTIL 3AM.
HE WENT TO COLLEGE, AND WAS HIRED AS A PROFESSOR.
HIS DAD WAS PROUD, BUT DID NOT TELL HIM THAT WITH WORDS.
HE BELIEVES THAT GROWING UP IN THE LIBRARY MADE HIM THE MAN HE IS TODAY.
THERE WAS A CHILD WHO GREW UP IN A LIBRARY.
HIS FATHER WAS THE JANITOR AND HE KEPT THE PLACE SPOTLESS
HE EVEN WAXED THE TOP OF THE BOOK SHELVES.
HE NEVER WANTED TO BRING FRIENDS HOME BECAUSE HE WAS EMBARESSED OF HIS HOUSE.
BUT HE GOT TO READ ALL THE BOOKS ANYTIME HE WANTED
HE WENT ON TO BE THE FIRST ONE IN HIS FAMILY TO COMPLETE COLLEGE.
HIS DAD WAS NOT VERBALLY EXCITED ABOUT HIS NEW JOB, BUT YOU COULD STILL TELL HE WAS PROUD.
THE BOY CANNOT IMAGINE GROWING UP ANYWHERE ELSE.
